Hawks spokesperson Hangwani Mulaudzi says their probe will not be limited to just the Eastern Cape. JOHANNESBURG The Hawks are zooming in on alleged corruption at several municipalities in the Eastern Cape.The unit says it s launched the investigations after reports of widespread corruption at both local and district municipalities in the province.Hawks spokesperson Hangwani Mulaudzi says their probe will not be limited to just the Eastern Cape. There will be other provinces that we will be visiting. Last week, 14 civil servants on charges of fraud and corruption in Johannesburg.